{
  "stem": "15197.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "If you wrote so many articles, and the writing is fine, write a book.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this, the articles were the base.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I started a book when deportation started.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I didn't go back from before the war, because this was really the knock.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The deportation was the main difference which cut off life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my book, which I wrote, I wrote by myself in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was later translated into Hebrew, and then into Spanish, and then into English.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then, not long ago, to Japanese.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So of all the languages.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And it is a little bit, for me, a surprise that now, more and more is being taught about the Holocaust, that in the beginning, when I wrote the book.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I remember when I wrote the book, and they wanted to publish this in English, the English publisher said, it's no interest for Holocaust literature at that time.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And this was 10 years after the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Today, 50 years after, is more awareness what took place than it was right after the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And my interest now, when I start reading what people are writing or talking about the Holocaust, is special about armed resistance and about the people went like sheep to the slaughter, was such a resentment that I dedicated a lot of talking how the real situation in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "How the 1,000 instances of resistance Jews put up, about what so little is known, and not even recognized in today's time, when violence is constantly on the daily agenda.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And Ben also-- Ben, my husband, Benjamin-- he also dedicated in organizing commemorations.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He organized, each year, a large public commemoration.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Once, two years ago, President Clinton came.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Vice President Gore then came.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Thousands of people are always present.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
